<p>In PHP how do you know if you should use each form of echo, and what is the proper uses for each:</p>  <p>with the period:</p>  <pre><code> echo"&lt;div&gt;         &lt;img src='".$row['image']."'&gt;         ".$row['text']."     &lt;/div&gt; </code></pre>  <p>with the comma:</p>  <pre><code>echo"&lt;div&gt;     &lt;img src='",$row['image'],"'&gt;     ",$row['text']," &lt;/div&gt; </code></pre>  <p>with the {}:</p>  <pre><code>echo"&lt;div&gt;     &lt;img src='". {$row['image']} ."'&gt;     ". {$row['text']} ." &lt;/div&gt; </code></pre>  <p>preset:</p>  <pre><code>$image=$row['image']; $text=$row['text'];     echo"&lt;div&gt;         &lt;img src='$image'&gt;         $text     &lt;/div&gt; </code></pre>  <p>More specifically I'm looking for the difference in how PHP will add the text to the HTML dump on the front end.</p>